    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.34a"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">207 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">34</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">DAVID STARR JORDAN
                        <lb/>
                    STANDFORD UNIVERISTY <add>P.O.</add>
                        <lb/>
                    CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>December 9th, 1918.</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Neihardt,</addrLine>
                
                            <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I shall be delighted to see your review, even though it is limited on every side by the conviction of your editor that God made for us a cosmos devoted to <hi rend="underline">Starrheit</hi>. This word in a forgotten tongue was not derived from my middle name, but from a shorter word which means, politically, "stalled in the bogs of the Middle Ages".</p>
                
                <p>I am always thankful for your friendly sympathy, even if you cannot say everything that you think. I have found a few limitations also.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>David Starr Jordan</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.34b"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">DAVID STARR JORDAN
                        <lb/>
                    STANFORD UNIVERSITY <add>P.O.</add>
                        <lb/>
                    CALIFORNIA</hi> 
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    PALO ALTO, CAL.
                    DEC 10
                    6-304
                    1918
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>2 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S.POSTAGE 2 CENTS 2</p>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>1 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES 1 ONE CENT <unclear cert="high">1</unclear></p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Neihardt,</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Bancroft,</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <note place="bottom" type="curatorial">Found in <hi rend="underline">Democracy</hi> and <hi rend="underline">World Relations</hi> &#8212; David Starr Jordan  <hi rend="caps">NY</hi> &#8212; World Book Co. 1918</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
